(Correction
    "NOTA is a way to write a Rust schema. A Rust struct has positional fields and does NOT require being inside a variant. The 'every record needs a PascalCase head' rule I quoted from nota/README.md is a falsehood — an agent hallucination in the spec. NOTA records (Rust structs at a known schema position) can be written positionally without naming the type; the schema position determines the type. The README and the nota-design.md skill both need this correction; my recent addition to skills/nota-design.md repeated the hallucination and needs softening."
    "Then the readme is wrong because nota is just a way to write a rust schema. And in Rust, there's a thing called a struct, and a struct is just a struct. It has fields, it has positional fields. Not every struct needs to be in a variant. That's a falsehood, and it's an agent hallucination that needs to be eradicated."
