(Clarification
    "NOTA codec enforces strict separation: NotaEnum requires all-unit variants and serializes/parses bare PascalCase; NotaSum requires all-data-carrying variants and serializes/parses `(VariantName fields…)`. The derive panics on mixed enums (nota-derive/src/nota_sum.rs:91: 'NotaSum does not support unit variants; use NotaEnum'). The gap surfaced by the psyche's reaffirmation: empty-struct variants in NotaSum (e.g. `TailnetClient {}` in horizon-rs/lib/src/proposal/services.rs) currently serialize as `(TailnetClient)` because the codec sees a struct variant with zero fields, not as bare per the no-data semantics. The author's intent (`non-data-carrying variants don't have surrounding parenthesis`) implies one of three fixes: (a) codec relaxes the NotaSum all-data-carrying rule and accepts mixed enums with bare-for-unit serialization; (b) codec detects empty-struct variants in NotaSum and emits bare form; (c) the author splits any mixed service-role into two enums (one NotaEnum for unit roles, one NotaSum for configured roles) to fit the current codec without altering it. Goldragon's services vector contains both shapes today (`(TailnetClient)`, `(NixBuilder None)`) — the empty cases would migrate to bare under (a) or (b)."
    "non-data-carrying variants don't have surrounding parenthesis. make sure that is how the latest nota actually works, as this is how I *want it to work*"
    "Verification follow-up to the 2026-05-20 15:30 NOTA reclarification. Reading nota-codec/src/decoder.rs (read_pascal_identifier line 122, expect_record_head line 201) and nota-derive/src/nota_sum.rs (line 91 panic) confirms the strict-but-mixed-forbidden architecture. Records the empty-struct-variant edge case the psyche's rule does not fully cover under the current derive split."
    Maximum
    2026-05-20 16:00)
